W. B. PINE v. UNITED STATES of America et al. No. 1781. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Oct. 10, 1938. C. B. McCrory, of Okmulgee, Old., for appellant. Cleon A. Summers, U. S. Atty., of Muskogee, Old.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appellee, United States of America, at appellant’s costs, for failure to prosecute.
